<前言><![CDATA[]]></前言>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard is prescribed in accordance with the provisions of Article 17 of the Act Governing Food Sanitation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The disposable chopsticks referred in this standard are those chopsticks made from bamboo or wood, intended for direct usage without washing or rinsing, and shall not be re-used.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[No discoloration, off odor and flavor, contamination, mould, pest diseases, foreign matter orfibre fall off shall be found in disposable chopsticks.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The sulphur dioxide residue of the disposable chopsticks shall not exceed 500 ppm.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Hydrogen peroxide and diphenolshall not be detected in the disposable chopsticks.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard shall be implemented from December 1, 2007.
The amended articles hereof shall come into effect as of the day of promulgation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
